String(exportTitle) : ''; if (t) { const safeTitle = t.replace(/</g, '<').replace(/>/g, '>'); if (/<title[\s\S]*?<\/title>/i.test(htmlStr)) { htmlStr = htmlStr.replace(/<title[\s\S]*?<\/title>/i, '<title>' + safeTitle + ''); } else if (/]*>/i.test(htmlStr)) { htmlStr = htmlStr.replace(/]*)>/i, '' + safeTitle + ''); } } // Print from a same-origin about:blank iframe so the app page stays intact. const iframe = document.createElement('iframe'); iframe.style.position = 'fixed'; iframe.style.right = '0'; iframe.style.bottom = '0'; iframe.style.width = '0'; iframe.style.height = '0'; iframe.style.border = '0'; iframe.setAttribute('aria-hidden', 'true'); const cleanup = () => { try { iframe.remove(); } catch(_){} }; // Set onload BEFORE attaching to DOM (important in Chrome) iframe.onload = () => { try { const win = iframe.contentWindow; const doc = iframe.contentDocument || (win && win.document); if (!doc) throw new Error('Cannot access print frame document'); doc.open(); doc.write(htmlStr); doc.close(); // Also set document title after write as a fallback try { if (t) doc.title = t; } catch(_) {} // Allow layout to settle before opening print dialog setTimeout(() => { try { win && win.focus(); win && win.print(); } finally { setTimeout(cleanup, 1500); } }, 120); } catch (e) { console.error(e); cleanup(); alert('PDF export failed. String(Math.round(n)) : String(n)) + 'g'; } const seriesTitle = document.getElementById('recipeSeries')?.selectedOptions?.[0]?.textContent || (data && data.series) || 'Ink-Recipe'; const recipeTitle = (data && data.name) || document.getElementById('recipeName')?.value || 'Recipe'; const totalLabel = formatScaledTotal(data && data.targetTotal); const exportTitle = safeFilename(seriesTitle) + '_' + safeFilename(recipeTitle) + '_' + safeFilename(totalLabel); const htmlStr = buildPrintHtml(data); // macOS Chrome: the Save dialog often uses the *top-level* document title as the default filename. // Temporarily set it to the exportTitle, then restore shortly after. const __prevDocTitle = document.title; try { document.title = exportTitle; } catch(_){} printHtml(htmlStr, exportTitle); setTimeout(() => { try { document.title = __prevDocTitle; } catch(_){} }, 1500); } catch (err) { console.error(err); alert('PDF export failed.
